Hi! I have noticed that there has been no activity on this project for a while.

* There has been no commit to master since June 2016;
* New issues are not answered;
* Pull requests are not reviewed.

Technical debt is accumulating:
* The master branch will not work out with new versions of the dependencies;
* The library is not tested against newer versions of Django;
* Users have to maintain their own branché

eulxml is an excellent library and we (@erudit) use it in production. I would like to know:

* Does @emory-libraries has any plans to resume work on eulxml in the future?
* If not, how can the community help maintaining the library?

